Testing, part I: inputs. You can create tests for vScheme code.

Benchmarking. You can create or port a benchmark.

Benchmarking in production. You can port a benchmark to a production system.

Testing, part II: outputs. You understand what testing tells you about the functional capabilities of your system.

Performance tuning. You understand space-time tradeoffs in garbage collection.

Performance. You understand what benchmark performance tells you about your system.

Testing and performance combined. You can achieve a combination of functionality and performance.

Performance in production. You understand how your system compares with a production system.
